Kh4 Ra3 {and Black has counterplay}) 18... Rc2 19. Kf3 d5 $1 20. exd5 (20. Rxd5
a6 21. Nd6 Rc3+ {equalizes}) 20... a6 {and White's passed pawn is probably not
enough to win against best defence.}) (17. Rxd6 Bxc3 18. bxc3 Rxc3+ 19. Rd3 Rc2
20. Rd2 Rac8 {and a draw could be agreed. --- It's worth noting that White, if
he wishes, can virtually force a draw against a higher rated player in these
lines - but why not play for a win?}) 17... Kf8 18. Rd2 Rc6 ({Premature is} 
