.}) 14. O-O Qa5 ({A couple of other moves have been tried:} 14... Qb6+ 15. Rf2
Qc5 16. b3 Rae8 17. Nd5 Nb4 18. Nxb4 Qxb4 {½-½ W.Martz-F.Visier Segovia,
Arrecife de Lanzarote 1974, but White should play on with} 19. Qd4 a6 20. Rd1 {
with a steady pull due to the space advantage.}) (14... Rc8 15. Kh1 Qa5 ({or} 
15... a6 16. Qd2 Na5 17. b3 Nc6 18. Rf3 Qa5 19. f5 Qe5 20. Raf1 Nd4 21. Rd3 Nc6
