Bb2 {is only equal in view of White's pawn weaknesses}) 17... Qxd1 18. Rxd1 Bf8
19. e6 Rfa7 20. Rd3 Bxc5 21. Bxc5 Rc7 22. e7 Re8 23. Rd5 a5 24. f4 b4 25. Kg2
Rb7 26. Rd4 Kf7 {and despite White's two pawns for the exchange, I don't see a
win for him; in fact, White has to be careful lest Black activate his 2-1
