{Donald Byrne had the misfortune to be on the losing side of two of the most
famous Grünfelds ever played: The "game of the century" loss to young Bobby
Fischer (where Byrne was White) in 1956, and now this, where he took the Black
side only to lose to Keres at his most brilliant!} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 d5
4. Nf3 Bg7 5. e3 O-O ({Since this chapter is devoted to various avoidances of
the main tabiya seen in Chapter 7, I will mention a few deviations as we go.
