12. Rc1 Bc6 13. O-O Nd7 14. b4 O-O-O 15. Qb2 Kb8 16. Nd4 Bd5 17. Nb5 Qc6 18.
Qa3 a6 19. Nd4 Qc7 20. b5 e5 21. b6 Qc8 22. c6 {1-0.}) 6. cxd5 ({Instead of
exchanging like this and putting the king's bishop on the active square c4, it
is possible to develop that piece immediately to e2. However, Black can then
set up a reversed Tarrasch position where the extra tempo is not significant:} 
6. Be2 c5 7. O-O cxd4 8. exd4 Nc6 9. h3 ({or} 9. Re1 Bg4 10. cxd5 Nxd5 11. h3
Be6 12. Bf1 Rc8 13. Bg5 h6 14. Be3 Nxc3 15. bxc3 Na5 16. Qc1 Kh7 17. Qa3 Qc7 {
