...Qc7. In both cases Black will get a reasonable game." --- With all due
respect to the master of this variation, I have to disagree. In the 7...Nxc3
variation, Black can equalize with a few accurate moves, and will then have
reasonable counterplay. In the 7...Nb6 variation, White gets a prolonged
initiative, while Black will be forced onto the defensive for the foreseeable
future. --- Although White's advantage is not great in the 7...Nb6 lines, the
difference to a practical player is quite large: Black has to defend and
suffer, while with Korchnoi's 7...Nxc3, Black can find his own play. In other
