a3 Qe7 15. Ba2 Nac4 16. Bg5 Bf6 17. Bxf6 Qxf6 18. Qe2 Nd6 19. h3 c5 20. Qe3 Bd7
21. Nd2 Rac8 {and White's passed pawn gives him a big positional advantage.
White went on to win in V.Burmakin-M.Zelic, Bled 1994.}) (11... Bg4 12. h3 Bxf3
(12... Nxb3 13. axb3 Bd7 14. Be3 f5 {would have held White to a slight edge})
13. Qxf3 Nac4 14. Qe2 Nd6 15. a4 a6 16. Be3 Nd7 17. a5 Kh8 18. Rac1 f5 19. exf5
